Package: tout
Title: Optimal Sample Size and Progression Criteria for Three-Outcome Trials
Version: 1.0.2
Authors@R: 
    person("Duncan", "Wilson", , "d.t.wilson@leeds.ac.uk", 
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7949-8718"))
Description: Find the optimal decision rules (AKA progression criteria)
    and sample size for clinical trials with three (stop/pause/go)
    outcomes. Both binary and continuous endpoints can be accommodated,
    as can cases where an adjustment is planned following a pause outcome. 
    For more details see Wilson et al. (2024) <doi:10.1186/s12874-024-02351-x>.
